      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 170: Nodes skipped by `canTryConnect()` are not scheduled for retry when `nextRetry` expires; they will only be retried if some unrelated event later calls `maintainBuckets()`. If the swarm becomes idle after all candidates enter backoff, a node can remain untried indefinitely even after the 30s/6h window expires. Track the earliest skipped `nextRetry` while maintaining buckets and schedule a timer/job to call `maintainBuckets()` then, or ensure the existing maintenance loop runs at a bounded interval shorter than the backoff base.",
